http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Two-boys-drown-in-canal/article14018742.ece

Two boys drowned in the Yagachi Left Bank Canal at Chikkabedikere, near Belur, on Saturday. They were identified as Mohammed (13) and Naveed (12), residents of Nehru Nagar in Belur town. They were students of Arabic school in Chikkamagaluru. They went to the canal after school hours. It is said that they had not informed their parents about it.As the boys, who did not know swimming, struggled and cried for help, some people jumped into water to rescue them, but could not save the boys. The bodies were recovered and shifted to Belur hospital for post-mortem. The Belur police have registered a case.